    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36a.43"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">43</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA-LINCOLN
                        <lb/>
                    LINCOLN, NEBRASKA 68508
                        <lb/>
                
                    DEPARTMENT OF ENGLISH</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 5, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>In 1964 or 1965 you read your poems at Concordia Teachers College in Seward; I was in the audience that night. In fact, before your reading, you autographed two of your books for me. I sent you this little chap-book of mine in return, but I sent to an address in Ogallala where I thought you lived.</p> 
                
                <p>I am dropping this copy off to you in return for your copies,which I enjoyed very, very much. I especially enjoyed your lyric and dramatic poems, some of which you read that stormy night in Seward so long ago.</p> 
                
                <p>I am working on a degree in English here at the University, but our home is in Thousand Oaks, California; however, since my two years in Seward, I have found Nebraska and Nebraskans compelling: hopefully I have been able to catch something of the flavor of the mid-west and plains in my poems.</p> 
                
                <p>If you ever have a spare moment I would love to talk poetry with you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Cordially,</salute>
                
                    <signed>J.T. Ledbetter</signed>
                    <signed>J.T. Ledbetter</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Andrews Hall 316</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Department of English</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA-LINCOLN              THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA AT OMAHA 
                        <lb/>
                                                        THE UNIVERSITY OF NEBRASKA MEDICAL CENTER</hi> 
                </fw>
                
            </div1>
